# Slow Performance — Windows 10/11

## Checks
- Task Manager CPU & Memory usage  
- Startup apps  
- Windows Update  
- Disk usage  
- Malware scan  

## Resolution
Disabled heavy startup apps  
Cleared temp files  
Installed Windows updates  
Performance restored

# Blue Screen of Death (BSOD) — Initial Analysis

## Symptoms
- System restarts randomly
- Blue screen error codes

## Diagnostics
1. Checked Event Viewer  
2. Reviewed Stop Code  
3. Ran Memory Diagnostic  
4. Updated drivers  

## Resolution
Faulty driver → updated to latest version → BSOD resolved.

# High CPU Usage — Troubleshooting

## Steps
1. Identified process in Task Manager  
2. Ended unnecessary background apps  
3. Checked for malware  
4. Restarted affected service  

## Resolution
Stuck background process → ended & restarted → normal CPU levels restored.
